		<description>Recently I had the pleasure of being interviewed by Dr. Carolyn Miller of the blog talk radio show Getting Good at Life. I got to share my tips for increasing your bottom line in 2012. It was a rewarding experience and I feel fortunate to be able to have shared my insights with those who [...]</description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<!-- Start Shareaholic LikeButtonSetTop Automatic --><!-- End Shareaholic LikeButtonSetTop Automatic --><p>Recently I had the pleasure of being interviewed by Dr. Carolyn Miller of the blog talk radio show <a href="http://www.blogtalkradio.com/drcarolynmiller" target="_blank"><em>Getting Good at Life</em></a>. I got to share my tips for increasing your bottom line in 2012. It was a rewarding experience and I feel fortunate to be able to have shared my insights with those who are looking to increase their bottom lines in 2012.</p>
<p><a href="http://drcarolynmiller.com/news/index.php?id=2" target="_blank">Dr. Carolyn Miller</a> is a psychologist, speaker and life coach who has a passion for helping others live the best life possible. For nearly 20 years, Dr. Carolyn has provided consultation both nationally and internationally in her work with businesses, government, non-profits, churches, and universities. Dr. Miller skillfully employs psychological, inspirational and strategic approaches to her mission of personal empowerment.</p>
<p>We discussed how in 2012 smalls businesses struggles with really making their presence known. Branding was difficult for small businesses because many did not know how to brand themselves. I shared my tips on how to make a change in 2012 and become prosperous.</p>
<p><strong><em>So what are you going to do in 2012 to get your brand into the minds and hands of your target audience?</em></strong></p>
<p>Check out this radio chat below to learn more about my thoughts and tips that will make a difference in the small business world in 2012:</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
