		<item>
		<title>Businesses Must Connect with their Customers</title>
		<link>http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/SocialMediaMarketingForBusiness/~3/0dhd74uu-LU/</link>
		<comments>http://kimbeasley.com/2012/01/27/businesses-must-connect-with-their-customers/#comments</comments>
		<pubDate>Fri, 27 Jan 2012 12:00:34 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>Kim Beasley</dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[Facebook]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Social Media Marketing]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Social Networking]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Mark Zuckerberg]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[social media]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://kimbeasley.com/?p=2232</guid>
		<description>Businesses today must be more &amp;#8220;social&amp;#8221; when to comes to doing business. Customers want to interact with people and they want to get to know the businesses that they are dealing with on a social level. Any business who does not do this is only hurting themselves at the end of the day. This is [...]</description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<!-- Start Shareaholic LikeButtonSetTop Automatic --><!-- End Shareaholic LikeButtonSetTop Automatic --><p>Businesses today must be more &#8220;social&#8221; when to comes to doing business. Customers want to interact with people and they want to get to know the businesses that they are dealing with on a social level. Any business who does not do this is only hurting themselves at the end of the day. This is a vital part of doing business today in an era of technology.</p>
<p>Mark Zuckerberg,CEO of Facebook explained it best in this video clip:</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>[There is a video that cannot be displayed in this feed. <a href="http://kimbeasley.com/2012/01/27/businesses-must-connect-with-their-customers/">Visit the blog entry to see the video.]</a></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>We all want to feel connected to someone and something. So it&#8217;s only natural that this is spilling over into the business world. Why do you think more and more businesses are creating pages on Facebook, Google+ and other platforms? It&#8217;s because there is something very powerful about being social.</p>
<p>Ask yourself how social you are with your target audience and current customers? What can you do to become more social?</p>
